 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Lead Counsel, Privacy AI Facebook 631 reviews Austin, TX Facebook 631 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Facebook is seeking a talented attorney to work on Facebook’s privacy legal team to advise the company on privacy and data protection issues relating to its artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies. This role is product-focused and will involve working closely with cross-functional teams to build artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies with a privacy-forward design. This will involve learning about the technologies underpinning a wide range of AI and ML product and research initiatives, identifying and investigating key design elements, coordinating with subject matter experts and regional counsel, and providing practical, actionable advice that mitigates risks under global privacy laws.
 Develop and maintain subject matter expertise in emerging regulations governing AI and ML, as well as existing privacy and data protection laws (including state and federal consumer protection and privacy laws, GDPR and other global privacy laws) and advise on the impact of the same on Facebook’s business 
Work closely with product counsel and product teams to guide privacy-forward product development and evaluate the impact of privacy laws, regulatory guidance and enforcement actions 
Drive high-profile and high-impact projects involving privacy analysis and compliance with cross-functional stakeholders across Facebook's business, policy, legal, communications, security, and other departments 
Develop regulatory strategy for global privacy regulators in connection with new product features and initiatives and maintain Facebook’s ongoing privacy-by-design processes 
Help to develop and conduct general and role-specific privacy trainings across Facebook 
J.D. degree (or foreign equivalent) and membership in at least one US state bar 
5+ years of legal experience, including at a law firm and/or in-house experience 
Experience advising on privacy legal risks and mitigations 
Experience with global privacy laws, regulations, and industry guidelines, especially as it relates to the field of artificial intelligence 
In-house experience with applicable product counseling, compliance, litigation, or regulatory teams, especially within social media, Internet, or other companies in the tech sector 
Experience prioritizing work and providing advice under deadlines 
Business judgment and client counseling experience 
Experience working cross-functionally to advance projects in a multi-stakeholder environment 
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started. 
